\n    \n        \n    \n\n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                                                                                                                                                                                                        \n            \n    \n    \n        \n                \n                    \n                        \n                                    \u003cdiv id=\"article-body\" itemprop=\"articleBody\"\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv id=\"custom_block_0\"\u003e\n\n                    \u003ch3\u003eSummary\u003c/h3\u003e\n        \n            \u003cdiv\u003e    \u003cul\u003e\n                    \u003cli\u003e\n                                        Google\u0026#39;s latest Gemini feature allows users to ask contextual questions about specific locations in Google Maps.\n                        \u003c/li\u003e\n                    \u003cli\u003e\n                                        The Ask about place chip in Gemini integrates with Google Maps, providing information about businesses and restaurants.\n                        \u003c/li\u003e\n                    \u003cli\u003e\n                                        While still in early stages, the integration works well for specific locations, with potential for more functionality as it develops.\n                        \u003c/li\u003e\n            \u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n    \n        \n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGoogle\u0026#39;s newest Gemini feature ties directly into Google Maps. It gives users the ability to ask contextual questions about specific places, such as \u0026#34;Does this store carry milk?\u0026#34; \u003c/p\u003e            \n    \n                    \n                        \n                \n    \n                                        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                \n        \n    \u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"ad26-4755-a448c1f8ceb4\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\n        \n        \n                        \t                \n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/google-maps-vs-waze/\"\u003e\n\t\n\t\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/03/waze-vs-google-maps-hero.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/03/waze-vs-google-maps-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/03/waze-vs-google-maps-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/03/waze-vs-google-maps-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/03/waze-vs-google-maps-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/03/waze-vs-google-maps-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/03/waze-vs-google-maps-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/03/waze-vs-google-maps-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/03/waze-vs-google-maps-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"1680\" height=\"840\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"waze and google maps logos superimposed on maps\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/03/waze-vs-google-maps-hero.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/03/waze-vs-google-maps-hero.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\n\n        \n                    \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n\n                \n                 \n                \t\n\u003ch5\u003e\n\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t        \t\t\t\t\n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/google-maps-vs-waze/\" title=\"Google Maps vs. Waze\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\n\t\t\tGoogle Maps vs. Waze\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\u003c/h5\u003e\n\n                                                    \n                \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eWhich navigation app is better for you?\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\n\n                    \n\n\n                \n                \n                \n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n                \t\n\n\n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe feature appears as a new Ask about place chip when you launch Gemini from within Google Maps (via \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidauthority.com/gemini-ask-about-place-3537852/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eAndroid Authority\u003c/a\u003e). You can query Gemini for information about restaurants, businesses, tourist traps, etc. At least, that is the idea, although the new feature is not yet available to everyone.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"how-the-ask-about-place-integration-works\"\u003e\n                        How the Ask about place integration works\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n    \n\n\n\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    \n    \n\n\u003cp\u003eYou can invoke Gemini directly in Google Maps by tapping on a place and then summoning Gemini on your device like you normally would. When the Gemini input bubble opens at the bottom of your screen, you will see a chip labeled \u0026#39;\u003cstrong\u003eAsk about place\u003c/strong\u003e.\u0026#39; Tapping it passes a Maps URL to Gemini, and it will understand what you\u0026#39;re referring to. Gemini will then answer questions like how to get there, what\u0026#39;s nearby, and menu details for restaurants. \u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eWe gave it a try and found the integration works best with specific businesses and locations. Broad queries about neighborhoods or entire cities don\u0026#39;t work. We also found it fell back on Google Search for some questions, especially more nuanced queries. However, it works surprisingly well most of the time.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eMy own test correctly identified that my local Mediterranean restaurant serves souvlaki. It also gave me a list of other menu items from the same place. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch3 id=\"it-39-s-still-early-but-shows-promise\"\u003e\n            It\u0026#39;s still early but shows promise\n    \u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\nThis \u003cstrong\u003eAsk about place\u003c/strong\u003e feature is still in an early rollout phase and may not be available across all accounts. Gemini may fail to load Maps context, or the chip may not even appear. We don\u0026#39;t know if Gemini Advanced is required for full functionality, although it seems as if it isn\u0026#39;t. My own tests worked, and I am not a     \n\n        \n\u003cspan data-id=\"1023877\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/gemini-advanced-guide/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eGemini Advanced\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n subscriber.    \u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eYou will need the Google app \u003cstrong\u003eversion 16.10.40\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003eGemini app version 1.0.686588308\u003c/strong\u003e, and \u003cstrong\u003eGoogle Maps version 25.12.01\u003c/strong\u003e. We will continue monitoring this as it develops into something incredibly useful. \u003c/p\u003e    \n    \n    \n    \n\u003c/div\u003e\n    \n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                    \n        \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n            \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
